<meta property="og:description" content="If we had the opportunity many people would likely decide that they would stay in their home for their entire lives. But with age this outcome will be dependent upon one&#039;s ability to find affordable and reliable home care. Changes to your home may also be needed, things such as stair lifts and bathroom handrails. But to be able to make claims for cash to pay for these things the local authority will make an assessment of you and your finances. This begs the question, who pays for this? The answer is, it depends upon your care and financial needs whom pays. On some occasions you will be entitled to partial or full payment from your local authority. Most of the time however, you will be expected to fund these things completely on your own, such as if you are wealthy or in relatively good health for your age or both. If you happen to be funding your home care you are able to pick whom your home care provider gets to be. The options vary but you can contact an agency to help you with your" />
